A Nigerian, who was out on bail in a drug case, has been arrested for alleged possession of narcotics worth over Rs 22 lakh (about N12 million) in Navi Mumbai, police said on Tuesday. The Navi Mumbai police have recovered amphetamine and methaqualone worth Rs 22.65 lakh from the accused, Annehe Kingsley Chinedu (37), Navi Mumbai Police Commissioner Bipin Kumar Singh said. Indian police The Anti-Narcotics Cell (ANC) of the Navi Mumbai police had received information about some persons arriving near an IT park at Turbhe on February 19 and laid a trap at the location, the official said. The police intercepted the accused, who was on a scooter and found 71g of amphetamine and 120g of methaqualone on him, Republic World reports. Chinedu, a native of Lagos in Nigeria, had earlier been booked for drug peddling and an offence was registered against him at Vashi police station.